title: Cloak AC-6 — undo reverts occurrence counters and message state
story: cloak-of-darkness
description: ADR-210 AC-6 (added Phase 6, additive to the frozen golden six).
  Undoing the first dark entry must roll back the first-time ordinal's
  trample along with the movement — occurrence counters and chord.state.*
  are world state, so undo needs no author-written code. The message reads
  intact (the win ending) afterward.

---

# Dark entry 1: first-time ordinal tramples the message
> south
[OK: contains "Blundering around in the dark isn't a good idea!"]

# Undo the entry: movement AND the trample roll back together
> undo
[EVENT: true, type="platform.undo_completed"]

> look
[OK: contains "Foyer of the Opera House"]

# Hang up the cloak and read: the message is intact again — the win
> west
[OK: contains "Cloakroom"]

> remove cloak
[OK: contains "You take off the velvet cloak"]

> hang cloak on hook
[OK: contains "put the velvet cloak on the brass hook"]

> east
[OK: contains "Foyer of the Opera House"]

> south
[OK: contains "Foyer Bar"]

> read message
[OK: contains "The message, neatly marked in the sawdust, reads"]
[OK: contains "You have won"]
[EVENT: true, type="story.victory"]
